CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 8, reads: "Attention State Liquor Control Board - How Many More Taverns Can Homewood-Brushton Stand?  'Crossroads Trio' - The liquor dispensing establishment at the left in the picture is situated near (center, left): The Tioga Tavern, and (right), The Rosedale Tavern, all at the intersection of Rosedale and Tioga Sts.... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Tioga Street at intersection of Rosedale Street with Bloomfield Market, Dairy Store, Bicycle Hobby Shop, and Rosedale Tavern, Homewood
